      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "a61a1867d763681b3470b6f6ca9535596855d8cc",
            "subject": "LU-3427 build: fix 'error handling' issues"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Keith Mannthey",
          "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-06-18 16:36:31.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-07-10 02:44:40.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-3403 llite: error of listxattr when buffer is small",
        "message": "LU-3403 llite: error of listxattr when buffer is small\n\nAccording to the standard, listxattr(2) should return -1\nand errno should be set to ERANGE if the size of the list\nbuffer is too small to hold the result. However ll_listxattr()\nwill return a value bigger than the size of buffer in some cases.\n\nLet's assume listxattr(2) returns SIZE when it is called with a\nlarge enough list buffer. If it's called again with a list buffer\nwhose size is smaller than SIZE but bigger than (SIZE - 12), then\nlistxattr(2) will return SIZE too. This patch fixes the problem.\nOriginal patch by Li Xi <pkuelelixi@gmail.com>\n\nSigned-off-by: Keith Mannthey <keith.mannthey@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ifb29ae900a5ee57dfde8781f7a008b6129c7bf91\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/6463\nTested-by: Hudson\nTested-by: Maloo <whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Li Xi <pkuelelixi@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
